profile_positions.description:
In this position I have a complex role of Product Launch process lead responsible for cross-functional collaboration and manager of an operational team working on both new launches and product changes.

 I As designated Product Launch process lead I am responsible for:
- steering, monitoring and supporting new Product Launch projects in all product categories by leading cross-departmental project status meetings within the European division and with the headquarters in Japan; 
- coordinating the operational launch preparation activities of the departments (Marketing, Quality Assurance, Regulatory Affairs, Supply Change Management, Technical Customer Service)  as well as the work of external translation and design agencies involved in the Product Launch Process; 
- planning and leading the approval stage gate meetings with key stakeholders (Board of Directors), 
- providing time-, budget- and risk-management for all business critical projects; 
- co-leading process optimization projects. 

Additionally, as a People Manager I have been responsible for supervising and coaching the Product Launch Specialists team that work on operational projects.

In this role I gained in-depth knowledge of the artwork development process and product specifications change management by working on hundreds of SKUs. Such projects require complex coordination skills and keen attention to details in order to reach a time- and and cost-efficent execution. 

Specialist in artwork (instruction manual and sales packaging) development for entire portfolio by: 
- coordinating new artwork development for in-parallel running various product launch projects; 
- preparing the artwork development planning and aligning with the R&D teams in Japan/China/Vietnam to ensure timely execution in line of the launch schedule;  
- managing product specification change (renovation) projects across various product categories (cardiovascular, respiratory, active healthcare) for in average 50 product versions (SKUs) per year; 
- coordinating the work of external translation and packaging design agencies and aligning with business partners to ensure local regulatory requirements are met; 
- maintaining product technical documentation database and providing business partners with up-to-date product documentation; 
- preparing product information sheets for regulatory and marketing/sales use;
- adhering to the QMS procedures and regularly updating tools (guidelines, SOPs, checklists) in line with the changes in the medical device regulations; 
Have contributed to more than 20 successful product launch projects in the last 5 years, including the global launches of innovative flagship products such as DuoBaby, Evolv and Complete.

In this role my main responsibility was to provide overall administrative support to the Product Launch team by:
- executing Product Specification Changes in active product portfolio; 
- gathering, sending and tracking marketing materials to business partners. 
-working on various Product Launch projects by coordinating operational tasks and creating/handling product documentation; 
- updating the centralized product launch documentation library; and 
- sample inventory management.
